**************************************************************
INSTALL (tested on Linux CentOS and Ubuntu only)

To compile on linux systems, type "./configure" then "make" in the root folder. This will generate the IReSISD executable in the "[ROOT_DIR]/bin" folder.

* Dependencies

The following librairies are required:

dcmtk (version 3.6.0 tested)
openCV (version 2.4.0 tested)
nifti (version 2.0.0 tested)
FFTW (version 3.3.3 tested)
openMP


**************************************************************
USAGE

An XML file containing all the parameters of the program has to be provided to the program:
./IReSISD [xml_file]

Possible parameters are described in "[ROOT]/xml_examples/params_explained.xml", and examples of XML files may be found in the folder "[ROOT]/xml_examples/".
